MIN() -  returns the smallest value of the selected column
MAX() - returns the largest value of the selected column

MIN():
SELECT MIN(Column)
FROM TableName
WHERE Condition;

MAX():
SELECT MAX(Column)
FROM TableName
WHERE Condition;

To find the price of the cheapest product:
SELECT MIN(Price) AS SmallestPrice
FROM Products;

To find the price of the expensive product:
SELECT MAX(Price) AS LargestPrice
FROM Products;

Q. Use the MIN function to select the record with the smallest value of the Price column.
SELECT MIN(Price)
FROM Products;

Q. Use an SQL function to select the record with the highest value of the Price column.
SELECT MAX(Price)
FROM Products;
